==English==
===Etymology===
This [[idiom]] derives from the repentance of [[w:Holy Roman Empire|Holy Roman]] [[emperor|Emperor]] [[w:Henry IV, Holy Roman Emperor|Henry IV]] to [[w:Pope Gregory VII|Pope Gregory VII]] after his [[excommunication]] for appointing [[bishop]]s.

===Idiom===
'''going to Canossa'''
# [[submit|Submitting]] to the [[pope]].